{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7517ccd6-422d-473d-9beb-2d57a5d4911b","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` can't verify *which line* threw — a bug elsewhere could satisfy it\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the assertion to the exact call\n- You can inspect the exception (message, inner exception, etc.)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92d6f5f3-2f9f-4971-b1c1-aef57cae6aeb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to modernize a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a straightforward knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"CFC7:2E7D56:14C9861:18278AF:69EC162B"},"id":"be4e41dc-7e3c-4b81-ba23-abd7dbbb7217","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:17:37.184Z","parentId":"283d33dc-427f-461b-93cb-f99fde3fe991"}
